
[1]caparison

   CAPARISON, n. A cloth or covering laid over the saddle or furniture of
   a horse, especially a sumpter horse or horse of state.

   CAPARISON, v.t.

   1. To cover with a cloth.

   2. To dress pompously; to adorn with rich dress.
